[Architecture|Topic=MemUnit_Living_Runtime|Aspect=core_io_resource_gate][Status=Active][Fact:MemUnit uses the bracket system and does not need to load full classes for every operation; bracket/tuple truth can route and identify work before class/code loading.][Fact:A missing required surface is Core IO: it gathers current system, hardware, IO, RAM, disk, resource, and environment facts so the orchestrator/system manager can decide whether an action is safe/possible before execution.][Rule:Before heavy actions, the orchestrator/resource gate must check available RAM, disk space, hardware/IO state, and related system limits; if resources are insufficient, it should block, warn the user, or choose a lower-cost plan.][Fact:Future system optimizer/junk/scrap cleaner may discover and remove scrap files to recover resources, but this is separate from the immediate resource gate.][Fact:The broader integrated system also includes UI, preferences, AI models, and in-RAM model surfaces, but these should not be overloaded into the current Boot patch until their boundaries are explicit.]

[Architecture|Topic=MemUnit_Living_Runtime|Aspect=execution_orchestration_repair_report_bus][Status=Active][Fact:MemUnit contains executor and orchestrator surfaces; executor runs code while orchestrator coordinates bracket/tuple packets through action/source/target style flow.][Fact:Failures are routed as packets to an Error Unit/Error Fixer path; the error path queries database history for prior matching errors/solutions, retrieves candidate unit/code/fix material, runs an in-memory iteration engine, tests/scores candidates, and writes solved candidates back beside the original as fixed/candidate rather than active until approved by the user or another AI.][Fact:Bracket packets must be tuple/structured because the orchestrator follows a specific flow and can identify action, source, target and related routing fields.][Fact:Ghost tags and magnetic signatures support magnetic radius matching, scoring, and discovering what units/code can connect to what.][Fact:Orchestration results and learned connection/proof/failure facts are written back to database truth so future routing learns what can, cannot, and might connect.][Fact:MemUnit also includes/reporting surface where a report class formats execution results and routes them to configured outputs; output targets and formats are controlled by config, such as screen, file, database, all, PDF or other formats.][Fact:MemUnit runtime picture includes MemDB, MemBus, GUIDB, GUI bus, and dynamic GUI behavior where config file or config stored inside a database plays a central role.]

