[Architecture|Topic=MemUnit_Living_Runtime|Aspect=anti_drift][Status=Locked][Rule:Do not describe this architecture as merely a database, plugin registry, or file store. It is a living MemUnit-centered architecture: boot surface, config/setup, in-RAM SQLite truth, token/bracket execution surface, execution servers, error/report/repair loops, in-RAM models, Ghost gatekeeper, Tokai token AI, and external AI escalation only when deterministic repair cannot solve.]

[Architecture|Topic=MemUnit_Living_Runtime|Aspect=in_ram_agents][Status=Locked][Rule:Cascade lives inside the runtime picture; Ghost is the gatekeeper/checker; Tokai is token AI checking token behavior; in-RAM AI fix model repairs code; AI-on-AI learning model can go online and learn. Most operations should use deterministic VBSTYLE/bracket/tables rather than LLM guessing; LLMs are escalation tools, not the normal execution layer.]

[Architecture|Topic=MemUnit_Living_Runtime|Aspect=error_repair_loop][Status=Locked][Rule:Core error unit detects errors from runtime truth, looks up known error/fix rows, loads relevant file/class/function/candidate into in-RAM DB, starts test/iteration engine, and iterates repairs. If local iteration fails, in-RAM AI searches/learns online, stores findings in SQLite, produces new candidates, kills weak candidates, and retries. If still unresolved, external models such as OpenAI/Codex/Claude may be called as escalation, and returned fixes enter the same candidate/test/admit loop.]

[Architecture|Topic=MemUnit_Living_Runtime|Aspect=closed_loop_execution][Status=Locked][Rule:CLI/API sends token/bracket commands into in-RAM SQLite/MemUnit. SQLite/tables hold and mutate token/bracket truth. Execution unit consumes the routed token/bracket truth, runs admitted callable logic, returns results to the same in-RAM database. Report/error units watch this truth and respond.]

[Architecture|Topic=MemUnit_Living_Runtime|Aspect=store_engine][Status=Locked][Rule:The store engine stores source code, brackets, documentation, details, test proof, version truth, route/call truth, and any callable/compiled/cache bodies. Storage is not execution authority; MemUnit drives execution through bracket/table truth.]

[Architecture|Topic=MemUnit_Living_Runtime|Aspect=candidate_gate][Status=Locked][Rule:Candidate intake, VBSTYLE validation, AST scanning, and bracket scanning are one fixed gatekeeper set, conceptually one class or tightly unified authority with many methods. No admitted code slips around this gate. Code is either rejected with reasons or absorbed as tested VBSTYLE truth.]

[Architecture|Topic=MemUnit_Living_Runtime|Aspect=bracket_execution_truth][Status=Locked][Rule:MemUnit executes bracket-connected truth, not file-path guessing. Brackets/Ghost/tokens are the contract/routing/identity surface and connect to table rows/callable bodies. Do not invent a separate root registry when brackets already carry identity, location, class, method, function, route, and documentation truth.]

[Architecture|Topic=MemUnit_Living_Runtime|Aspect=core_authority_and_boot][Status=Locked][Rule:MemUnit is the first authority and living runtime center, not a last component and not a simple router. Without MemUnit boot/config/setup/in-RAM DB/execution/error/report surfaces, nothing starts. CLI/API connects to MemUnit; candidate intake, scanner, validator, store, execution, report, error, repair, AI assistance, and result writeback all operate through MemUnit.]

